<title>FRANCE: Merrill begins trading on Paris bourse May 16.</title>
<headline>Merrill begins trading on Paris bourse May 16.</headline>
<dateline>PARIS 1997-05-15</dateline>
<text>
<p>U.S. stock brokerage Merrill Lynch &amp; Co said on Wednesday that it would begin trading equities on the Paris bourse on Friday.</p>
<p>&quot;With the fourth-largest economy in the world and a growing private-pension system, France is rapidly becoming a stronghold for equity investment,&quot; Michel Fleuriet, managing director of Merrill Lynch in Paris, said in a statement.</p>
<p>Merrill Lynch became a member of the Paris bourse in December. It is a member now of 23 exchanges and covers more than 3,000 companies in 50 countries.</p>
